Giancarlo wrote:
> 
> Bruno wrote:
> 
> > Ultimate Oscillator
> >
> > Inputs:
> >
> > Name    Default Description
> > Avg1Len 7       Length of Average 1
> > Avg2Len 14      Length of Average 2
> > Avg3Len 28      Length of Average 3
> > Plot Names:
> > Plot1= Ultimate Oscillator
> 
> Can you translate this is a simple algebric form
> (or give a description of calculation with simple words)?
> Is it a sum of 3 momenta?
> Or are there moving averages in it?
> 
> (I don't use programs such as Metastock or Tradestation or whatever,
> I use Excel!)
> 
> Thanks
> 
> Giancarlo

Formula: =SUM((avg7),avg(14),avg(28))/3 
That is the most primitive way ;-)

You might square the individual averages,
sum the totals, then take the square root.

Consult any of the Excel newsgroups for better info!

P.S.  I experimented with something like this when "VISICALC"
was introduced (long time ago!) but the results proved
not any better than simply buying new moon, selling full moon.
Good luck, Bruno
